A:

It's because you are checking the text outside the event handler. The current condition check of text=='00:00' will only execute once when the script is loaded.
Here's the working javascript function
var date = $('#clock').data('countdown');
$('#clock').countdown(date, function (event) {
  $(this).html(event.strftime('%M:%S'));

  if(document.getElementById('clock').innerHTML === "00:00") {
    window.location.reload();
